The paper deals with the complexity classes P and NP, which are central to computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves Boolean satisfiability, which is a fundamental problem in computer science, and involves the construction of an artificial problem, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the construction of a restricted type X program, which could fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper involves the demonstration of theorems, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
